{"id":1061013907,"question_id":15,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"9Â months","timestamp":1695870199,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"29 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1061013907/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"3Sum","memory":"50.6 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public List<List<Integer>> threeSum(int[] nums) {\n        List<List<Integer>> res = new ArrayList<>();\n        int n = nums.length;\n        int low, high, sum, cur;\n        Arrays.sort(nums);\n\n        for(int i=0;i<n-2;i++){\n            if(i>0 && nums[i]== nums[i-1])\n                continue;\n            low = i+1;\n            high = n-1;\n            while(low<high){\n                sum = nums[i]+nums[low]+nums[high];\n                if(sum<0){\n                    low++;\n                }else if(sum>0){\n                    high--;\n                }else{\n                    res.add(Arrays.asList(nums[i], nums[low], nums[high]));\n                    low++;\n                    while(high>low && nums[low] == nums[low-1])\n                        low++;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        return res;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"3sum","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
